@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@storeId = 2
@cartId = 2
@orderId = 2

### CART (CUSTOMER)

# Add item to cart (creates cart if none exists, or adds to existing)
# storeId and unitPrice must match the product — snapshot is taken at add time
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 6,
  "storeId": {{storeId}},
  "unitPrice": 18000,
  "quantity": 2
}

### Add another item to cart
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 2,
  "storeId": {{storeId}},
  "unitPrice": 19000,
  "quantity": 1
}

### Get my cart
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/carts/me
Authorization: {{customerToken}}

### Remove single item from cart
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/carts/products
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cartId": {{cartId}},
  "productId": 1
}

### Clear cart (remove all items)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cartId": {{cartId}}
}

### Checkout — converts cart to order
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/carts/checkout
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cartId": {{cartId}}
}

### ORDER — customer view, list my orders
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me/orders
Authorization: {{customerToken}}

### ORDER — owner view, list orders for store
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/stores/orders/list
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": {{storeId}}
}

### Mark order as sold (OWNER)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/stores/orders/sold
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": {{storeId}},
  "orderId": {{orderId}}
}

### Cancel order (OWNER)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/stores/orders/cancel
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": {{storeId}},
  "orderId": {{orderId}}
}

### STATISTICS

### Revenue for store by month — UTC (OWNER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/stores/statistics/revenue
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": {{storeId}},
  "year": 2026,
  "month": 3
}

### Revenue for store by month — Seoul time (OWNER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/stores/statistics/revenue
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": {{storeId}},
  "year": 2026,
  "month": 3,
  "timezone": "Asia/Seoul"
}

### My spending by month — UTC (CUSTOMER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me/statistics/spending
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "year": 2026,
  "month": 3
}

### My spending by month — New York time (CUSTOMER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me/statistics/spending
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "year": 2026,
  "month": 3,
  "timezone": "America/New_York"
}

###

# =============================================================================
# HMAC Verification — order-service :8083
# =============================================================================

### HMAC-1: Direct to backend — no headers → 401 Missing HMAC headers
POST http://localhost:8083/api/carts/me
Authorization: {{customerToken}}

###

### HMAC-2: Through BFF — signed automatically → 200
POST http://localhost:8080/api/carts/me
Authorization: {{customerToken}}

###

### HMAC-3: Direct to backend — valid timestamp, wrong signature → 401 Invalid HMAC signature
< {%
  request.variables.set("nowMs", Date.now().toString());
%}
POST http://localhost:8083/api/carts/me
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
X-Bff-Timestamp: {{nowMs}}
X-Bff-Signature: deadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeef

###

### HMAC-4: Direct to backend — expired timestamp → 401 Request expired
POST http://localhost:8083/api/carts/me
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
X-Bff-Timestamp: 1000000000000
X-Bff-Signature: anything
